Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Maple, Siderperu, Telefonica, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-06-01T18:48:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/peru-stocks-atacocha-maple-siderperu-telefonica-volcan.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 2:30 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index dropped 6.4 percent to 20,180.53.
The MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 5.2 percent to 2,637.11.  Industrial stocks and utilities slumped on investor fears
that former military rebel Ollanta Humala may win the June 5
elections, said Javier Frisancho, a trader at Lima-based
brokerage Kallpa Securities SAB. Humala has said he will
renegotiate contracts with foreign companies if he’s elected.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, plunged 13 percent to 85 cents
after crude declined in New York.  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru
SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of Gerdau SA known as Siderperu, fell
12 percent to 1.27 soles. Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1
PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol YPF SA, dropped 10 percent to 1.65
soles.  Telefonica del Peru SAA (TELEFBC1)  (TELEFBC1 PE), the local unit of
Telefonica SA, fell 10 percent to 2.50 soles.  Casa Grande 
(CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer and a unit of
Gloria SA, dropped 9.2 percent to 14.90 soles after sugar
declined in New York.  Miners declined after copper, silver and zinc fell in New
York and  London .  Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of
Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., plummeted 12 percent to
$35.  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based
silver and zinc producer, dropped 7.8 percent to 1.07 soles.
Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s biggest zinc and
silver producer, fell 7.1 percent to 3 soles. Soc. Minera El
Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a silver and zinc producer, slid 6.8
percent to 38.70 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
